        "excerpt":"  Transcript The slides maker is one of the sample apps in Fizzygum. To open it, double click on the slide icon:   The starting slide has a toolbar and the “editing pencil” is highlighted. When clicked, the toolbar is hidden, for less clutter and easier reading:   Just click again to use the toolbar, drag anything out of it and put it in place:   You can resize any item by right-clicking on it, choosing the item you want to resize, and choosing “resize/move” from the menu:   You can change many properties of any item in the same way, for example the color of this map:   Once any item is added, the slide will lock its proportions, so when the slide is resized all the items will keep their relative positions:   Let’s add a link now:   And finally, you can drop anything in the slides maker, try with the clock for example:   That’s it for the slides maker, make sure to check out other videos to see more examples of use such as embedding interactive graphs. ","categories": [],
